<span class="displaytext">santa fe, nm- new mexico governor (candidate full)'s today issued the following statement following the death of former russian president boris yeltsin, who died this morning at the age of 76. <p>"president yeltsin was larger than life in every way- an intense politician with a unique and bold style," said governor (candidate last). "he sensed the tide of change rising in his country and was a driving force behind the emergence of democracy there. president yeltsin enjoyed sweeping successes as well as crashing defeats and has left an indelible mark on world history." (candidate full) served 7 terms in the united states house of representatives, as well as us ambassador to the united nations and as secretary of energy, and was recently re-elected to a second term as governor of new mexico.</p></span>



